  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The chambers of commerce of\nSan Francisco and Los Angeles\nhave made a deal with the Harri-\nman railroads whereby the hoboes\nwho have as usual spent the winter\nand spring in California are to be\ntransported to Oregon and Wash\nington free of charge. Freight\ntrain crews have been instructed\nto let men ride north without\nmolestation.\n\n\nAt the same time free soup kitch-\nems have been abolished in the\nprincipal California cities. More\nthan 1000 men have lately been\nsent through to Puget Sound, al\nthough the Northern Pacific is ten\ndering no gratuitOus transportation\nto the knights of the road from\nPortland."
    }
  ]
